com.paydiant.android.ui.service.deviceinfo

Class DeviceInfoServiceListenerAdapter

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.paydiant.android.ui.service.deviceinfo.DeviceInfoServiceListenerAdapter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IDeviceInfoServiceListener

    public class DeviceInfoServiceListenerAdapter
extends Object
implements IDeviceInfoServiceListener
    This class provides an empty implementation for IDeviceInfoServiceListener. Any classes that wants to use only a subset of the listener methods can override the relevant methods and use it as the interface implementation. 

     DeviceInfoServiceListenerAdapter deviceInfoServiceListenerAdapter = new DeviceInfoServiceListenerAdapter() {
 
    @Override
    public void onAddAdditionalDeviceInfoSuccess() {
    }
 
    @Override
    public void onDeviceInfoManagerServiceError(PaydiantException exception) {
    }
 };
 iDeviceInfoServiceListener.setDeviceInfoManagerListener(IDeviceInfoServiceListener deviceInfoServiceListener);
    Note: App developers are encouraged to use the ListenerAdapter implementations whenever possible as the Listener interfaces might get updated with new functionality/methods from one SDK release to the other. Therefore using a ListenerAdapter will make sure that there wont be any compilation issues due to unimplemented methods during a SDK upgrade.

    Since:
    4.5.0.1
    Author:
